      "id": "solid_state-nuclear-fission",
      "name": "BCS Superconductivity (Cooper Pairing)",
      "description": "BCS theory explains superconductivity below a critical temperature: a phonon-mediated attraction between electrons, when it overcomes Coulomb repulsion near the Fermi surface, binds them into Cooper pairs that condense into a coherent ground state; an energy gap opens, producing zero resistance and the Meissner effect.",
