      "id": "solid_state-nuclear-fusion",
      "name": "Phonons & Debye Heat Capacity",
      "description": "Lattice vibrations quantized as phonons set a crystal's heat capacity: normal modes have a dispersion that the Debye model approximates as linear up to a cutoff frequency; integrating the phonon density of states gives a specific heat scaling as T-cubed at low temperature and approaching the Dulong-Petit value at high temperature.",
      "graphType": "decision_flowchart",
      "domainContext": "Solid-state physics / lattice dynamics",
      "keywords": ["phonons", "Debye model", "specific heat", "lattice vibrations", "Dulong-Petit"],
